727080f-a.text:
Jamaica Avenue, at the S.E. corner of 212th Street, showing Starrs Hotel, formerly the "Fulton and First."  The last name was derived from the fact that Jamaica Avenue was known as Fulton Avenue and 212th Street as First Avenue.

P.L. Sperr
March 4, 1927

727084f-b.text:
Jamaica Ave., south side, at 212th Street, showing the B. Lane Hotel of 1873 in the foreground.  Dowden and Geo. Barb owned it in 1891 and 1896 respectively.  This is a set of four views; view No. 4 looks westward to about 207th Street, showing clearly in the foreground the S.E. and S.W. corners of 212th Street.

1922.
View 2: April 1925
Views 3 & 4: May 1923

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
